{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"nonisolated","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"foregroundStyle","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"S","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":">(","kind":"text"},{"text":"_","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"style","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"S","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"View","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"where","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"S","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ShapeStyle","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore10ShapeStyleP"},{"text":"\n","kind":"text"}]}]},{"kind":"parameters","parameters":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The color or pattern to use when filling in the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"foreground elements. To indicate a specific value, use "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Color"},{"type":"text","text":" or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ShapeStyle\/image(_:sourceRect:scale:)"},{"type":"text","text":", or one of the gradient"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"types, like"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ShapeStyle\/linearGradient(colors:startPoint:endPoint:)"},{"type":"text","text":". To set a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"style that’s relative to the containing view’s style, use one of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"semantic styles, like "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle\/primary"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}],"name":"style"}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"return-value","text":"Return Value","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A view that uses the given foreground style."}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use this method to style","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"foreground content like text, shapes, and template images","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(including symbols):","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["HStack {","    Image(systemName: \"triangle.fill\")","    Text(\"Hello, world!\")","    RoundedRectangle(cornerRadius: 5)","        .frame(width: 40, height: 20)","}",".foregroundStyle(.teal)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The example above creates a row of ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle\/teal","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" foreground","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"elements:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can use any style that conforms to the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" protocol,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"like the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle\/teal","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" color in the example above, or the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"ShapeStyle\/linearGradient(colors:startPoint:endPoint:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" gradient","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"shown below:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["Text(\"Gradient Text\")","    .font(.largeTitle)","    .foregroundStyle(","        .linearGradient(","            colors: [.yellow, .blue],","            startPoint: .top,","            endPoint: .bottom","        )","    )"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Tip","style":"tip","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you want to fill a single "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Shape","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" instance with a style,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"use the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Shape\/fill(style:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" shape modifier instead because it’s more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"efficient."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"OpenSwiftUI creates a context-dependent render for a given style.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"For example, a ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Color","isActive":true},{"text":" that you load from an asset catalog","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"can have different light and dark appearances, while some styles","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"also vary by platform.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Hierarchical foreground styles like "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ShapeStyle\/secondary"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"don’t impose a style of their own, but instead modify other styles."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"In particular, they modify the primary"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"level of the current foreground style to the degree given by"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the hierarchical style’s name."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"To find the current foreground style to modify, OpenSwiftUI looks for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the innermost containing style that you apply with the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"foregroundStyle(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" or the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View\/foregroundColor(_:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" modifier."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If you haven’t specified a style, OpenSwiftUI uses the default foreground"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"style, as in the following example:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["VStack(alignment: .leading) {","    Label(\"Primary\", systemImage: \"1.square.fill\")","    Label(\"Secondary\", systemImage: \"2.square.fill\")","        .foregroundStyle(.secondary)","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you add a foreground style on the enclosing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/VStack","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", the hierarchical styling responds accordingly:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["VStack(alignment: .leading) {","    Label(\"Primary\", systemImage: \"1.square.fill\")","    Label(\"Secondary\", systemImage: \"2.square.fill\")","        .foregroundStyle(.secondary)","}",".foregroundStyle(.blue)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When you apply a custom style to a view, the view disables the vibrancy"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"effect for foreground elements in that view, or in any of its child"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"views, that it would otherwise gain from adding a background material"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"— for example, using the "},{"code":"View\/background(_:ignoresSafeAreaEdges:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"modifier. However, hierarchical styles applied to the default foreground"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"don’t disable vibrancy."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ForEach\/foregroundStyle(_:)"},"metadata":{"symbolKind":"method","platforms":[{"introducedAt":"13.0","unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"iOS","beta":false},{"introducedAt":"10.15","unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"macOS","beta":false},{"introducedAt":"13.0","unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"tvOS","beta":false},{"introducedAt":"1.0","unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"visionOS","beta":false},{"introducedAt":"6.0","unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"watchOS","beta":false}],"extendedModule":"OpenSwiftUICore","externalID":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewPAAE15foregroundStyleyQrqd__AA05ShapeF0Rd__lF::SYNTHESIZED::s:15OpenSwiftUICore7ForEachV","remoteSource":{"fileName":"ForegroundStyleModifier.swift","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/OpenSwiftUIProject\/OpenSwiftUI\/blob\/main\/Sources\/OpenSwiftUICore\/Shape\/ShapeStyle\/ForegroundStyleModifier.swift#L112"},"title":"foregroundStyle(_:)","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"foregroundStyle","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"S","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":">(","kind":"text"},{"text":"S","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"t